## 16S rRNA preprocessing with QIIME2 and DADA2

Raw paired-end FASTQ files were processed using QIIME2. A manifest file was first generated to map each sample ID to its corresponding forward and reverse read files.

qiime tools import \
  --type 'SampleData[PairedEndSequencesWithQuality]' \
  --input-path manifest.tsv \
  --output-path demux-paired-end.qza \
  --input-format PairedEndFastqManifestPhred33V2

Read quality was assessed using:

qiime demux summarize \
  --i-data demux-paired-end.qza \
  --o-visualization demux-paired-end.qzv

Paired-end reads were denoised using DADA2 to remove low-quality reads, correct sequencing errors, merge paired reads, and remove chimeric sequences.

qiime dada2 denoise-paired \
  --i-demultiplexed-seqs demux-paired-end.qza \
  --p-trunc-len-f 240 \
  --p-trunc-len-r 220 \
  --p-trim-left-f 0 \
  --p-trim-left-r 0 \
  --p-n-threads 8 \
  --o-table table.qza \
  --o-representative-sequences rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-denoising-stats denoising-stats.qza

Representative sequences were taxonomically classified using a pre-trained SILVA 132 classifier.

qiime feature-classifier classify-sklearn \
  --i-classifier silva-132-99-nb-classifier.qza \
  --i-reads rep-seqs.qza \
  --o-classification taxonomy.qza

The feature table was collapsed to genus level.

qiime taxa collapse \
  --i-table table.qza \
  --i-taxonomy taxonomy.qza \
  --p-level 6 \
  --o-collapsed-table genus-table.qza

The genus-level table was exported for downstream analysis in R.

qiime tools export \
  --input-path genus-table.qza \
  --output-path exported-genus-table

biom convert \
  -i exported-genus-table/feature-table.biom \
  -o genus-table.tsv \
  --to-tsv
